Example 2: a method that takes an array of strings, and returns a string that is all those strings concatenated together

# Informal Pseudo-Code

Given an array of strings.

Create an empty string and assign it to a variable. 
Create a method that iterates through the array of strings one by one. 
- For each interation, append each element of the array collection to the string variable.
  
Return the string output variable. 


# Formal Pseudo-Code

START

# Given an array of strings

SET string_output = nil

SET iterator = 0

IF size of array != iterator
  append element of array at space "iterator" to string_output
  iterator = iterator + 1
ELSE
  break 

PRINT string_output

END
